			<description><![CDATA[<p>
	Software Quality Engineer</p>
<p>
	Giftango would like to add a Software Quality Assurance Engineer to our team. We are looking for detail oriented, smart, energetic people that can work with our team to create best in class solutions. The ideal candidate for this position is someone that is able to work within a fun and dynamic team environment and has experience building, managing, and maintaining automated test suites. You will be working with like-minded individuals who are redefining an industry by bringing about a revolution in how people interact with payment systems and mobile applications.</p>
<p>
	Giftango is an industry leading technology organization focused on powering the next generation of mobile and alternative payments, gift card fulfillment and marketing. We are a diverse team with an entrepreneurial spirit who believe in building quality software products and services. Giftango is currently one of the most exciting technology stories in Oregon and offers a fast growing company environment, significant learning opportunities across a number of different areas, and the ability to take-on a variety of projects. We are a company that believes in building strong corporate and employee culture just as much as building new and innovative products. Hey, work doesn&#39;t have to be boring! If you believe in a &ldquo;work hard, play hard&rdquo; philosophy and are excited by the thought of knowing that what you do will play a crucial role in the overall success of the business, please contact us.<br />
	<br />
	Responsibilities:</p>
<ul>
	<li>
		Contribute to, and execute test implementation, test strategy, test plans and test designs</li>
	<li>
		Research, analyze, and report software defects</li>
	<li>
		Collaborate, define tasks, estimate, and provide direction with internal and external resources</li>
	<li>
		Provide quality assurance evaluation and input through active participation in the design, development, and end user testing of the applications</li>
	<li>
		Implement and maintain test automation suites</li>
	<li>
		Conduct feature testing, regression testing, boundary testing, and performance testing</li>
	<li>
		Provide troubleshooting and support to developers, product teams, and technical support</li>
	<li>
		Work with diverse marketing, operations, and development teams consisting of software architects, developers, customers, and managers, to analyze and solve key feature issues and rollouts.</li>
	<li>
		Provide strategic guidance in relation to Q/A&rsquo;s role in the SDLC and quality resource management.</li>
</ul>
<p>
	Requirements:</p>
<ul>
	<li>
		BS degree in Computer Science or related field, or equivalent work experience</li>
	<li>
		Working experience with test automation tools such as NUnit or MSTest</li>
	<li>
		Working knowledge of C#</li>
	<li>
		3 years&rsquo; work experience in software testing and quality assurance</li>
	<li>
		Experience with Selenium, WatiN, WatiR or similar QA tools</li>
	<li>
		Strong written and verbal communication skills</li>
	<li>
		Experience working in an iterative, agile development process</li>
	<li>
		Testing experience on multiple platforms and browsers &ndash; (Windows, Mac, IE, Safari, Chrome, Firefox)</li>
	<li>
		Working experience with load, performance, and stress testing</li>
	<li>
		Working knowledge of quality assurance and quality control methodologies</li>
	<li>
		Experience with black box and white box testing</li>
</ul>
<p>
	Strong Preference to candidates with:</p>
<ul>
	<li>
		Experience with Microsoft Product Development Life Cycle methodology</li>
	<li>
		Testing experience with web based ecommerce products</li>
	<li>
		Experience working with Microsoft TFS</li>
</ul>
<p>
	<br />
	Working Conditions:</p>
<p>
	This position is located at our corporate headquarters in downtown Portland, Oregon. Please visit our website (http://giftango.com) for more information about Giftango. Giftango offers competitive benefits, stock options, compensation, and the opportunity to be part of an exciting technology organization going through a growth spurt.</p>
